messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Happy Birthday
messages.msgSnippet: Thanks, Sharon.  We just had a wonderful dinner at Red Lobster, one of my kid s favorite places. We shocked the waitress and all the folks in the waiting area.
messages.messageBody:
Thanks, Sharon. We just had a wonderful dinner at Red Lobster, one of
my kid's favorite places. We shocked the waitress and all the folks in
the waiting area. Janene ordered lobster and vegitables, with a
specific request for brocoli. Lexie the ultimate shrimp feast. My
kids just won't order off the kid's menu at RL. After Janene ordered,
we went in the waiting room. She saw the lobster and we had the
following conversation...

Janene: Are those the lobsters they serve?
Me: Yes.
J: and they die, uh, kill them?
me: yes (wondering if she was going to change her order).
J: and they cook them?
me. yes (becoming more worried)
J: OK, can you have them kill and cook me THAT one (pointing to a
particular lobster)....

not what I expected...

Joylyn
